verses.verse: To the <S%H5329>chief<s%> <S%H5329>Musician,<s%> A <S%H7892>Song<s%> or <S%H4210>Psalm.<s%> Make a joyful noise to <S%H430>God,<s%> <S%H3605>all<s%> you <S%H776>lands:<s%>
<S%H2167>Sing<s%> forth the <S%H3519>honor<s%> of his <S%H8034>name:<s%> <S%H7760>make<s%> his <S%H8416>praise<s%> <S%H3519>glorious.<s%>

<S%H559>Say<s%> to <S%H430>God,<s%> <S%H4100>How<s%> <S%H3372>terrible<s%> are you in your <S%H4639>works!<s%> through the <S%H7230>greatness<s%> of your <S%H5797>power<s%> shall your <S%H341>enemies<s%> <S%H3584>submit<s%> themselves to you.
<S%H3605>All<s%> the <S%H776>earth<s%> shall <S%H7812>worship<s%> you, and shall <S%H2167>sing<s%> to you; they shall <S%H2167>sing<s%> to your <S%H8034>name.<s%> <S%H5542>Selah.<s%>

<S%H3212>Come<s%> and <S%H7200>see<s%> the <S%H4659>works<s%> of <S%H430>God:<s%> he is <S%H3372>terrible<s%> in his <S%H5949>doing<s%> <S%H5921>toward<s%> the <S%H1121>children<s%> of <S%H120>men.<s%>

He <S%H2015>turned<s%> the <S%H3220>sea<s%> into <S%H3004>dry<s%> <S%H776>land:<s%> they <S%H5674>went<s%> through the <S%H5104>flood<s%> on <S%H7272>foot:<s%> <S%H8033>there<s%> did we <S%H8055>rejoice<s%> in him.

He <S%H4910>rules<s%> by his <S%H1369>power<s%> for <S%H5769>ever;<s%> his <S%H5869>eyes<s%> <S%H6822>behold<s%> the <S%H1471>nations:<s%> let not the <S%H5637>rebellious<s%> <S%H7311>exalt<s%> themselves. <S%H5542>Selah.<s%>
O <S%H1288>bless<s%> our <S%H430>God,<s%> you <S%H5971>people,<s%> and make the <S%H6963>voice<s%> of his <S%H8416>praise<s%> to be <S%H8085>heard:<s%>
Which <S%H7760>holds<s%> our <S%H5315>soul<s%> in <S%H2416>life,<s%> and <S%H5414>suffers<s%> not our <S%H7272>feet<s%> to be <S%H4132>moved.<s%>
For you, O <S%H430>God,<s%> have <S%H974>proved<s%> us: you have <S%H6884>tried<s%> us, as <S%H3701>silver<s%> is <S%H6884>tried.<s%>
You <S%H935>brought<s%> us into the <S%H4685>net;<s%> you <S%H7760>laid<s%> <S%H4157>affliction<s%> on our <S%H4975>loins.<s%>

You have caused <S%H582>men<s%> to <S%H7392>ride<s%> over our <S%H7218>heads;<s%> we <S%H935>went<s%> through <S%H784>fire<s%> and through <S%H4325>water:<s%> but you <S%H3318>brought<s%> us out into a <S%H7310>wealthy<s%> place.
I will <S%H935>go<s%> into your <S%H1004>house<s%> with <S%H5930>burnt<s%> offerings: I will <S%H7999>pay<s%> you my <S%H5088>vows,<s%>
<S%H834>Which<s%> my <S%H8193>lips<s%> have <S%H6475>uttered,<s%> and my <S%H6310>mouth<s%> has <S%H1696>spoken,<s%> when I was in <S%H6862>trouble.<s%>

I will <S%H5927>offer<s%> to you <S%H5930>burnt<s%> sacrifices of fatted <S%H4220>calves,<s%> with the <S%H7004>incense<s%> of <S%H352>rams;<s%> I will <S%H6213>offer<s%> <S%H1241>bullocks<s%> with <S%H6260>goats.<s%> <S%H5542>Selah.<s%>

<S%H3212>Come<s%> and <S%H8085>hear,<s%> <S%H3605>all<s%> you that <S%H3373>fear<s%> <S%H430>God,<s%> and I will <S%H5608>declare<s%> <S%H834>what<s%> he has <S%H6213>done<s%> for my <S%H5315>soul.<s%>
I <S%H7121>cried<s%> to him with my <S%H6310>mouth,<s%> and he was <S%H7318>extolled<s%> with my <S%H3956>tongue.<s%>
<S%H518>If<s%> I <S%H7200>regard<s%> <S%H205>iniquity<s%> in my <S%H3820>heart,<s%> the <S%H136>Lord<s%> will not <S%H8085>hear<s%> me:
But <S%H403>truly<s%> <S%H430>God<s%> has <S%H8085>heard<s%> me; he has <S%H7181>attended<s%> to the <S%H6963>voice<s%> of my <S%H8605>prayer.<s%>
<S%H1288>Blessed<s%> be <S%H430>God,<s%> <S%H834>which<s%> has not <S%H5493>turned<s%> away my <S%H8605>prayer,<s%> nor his <S%H2617>mercy<s%> from me.
